```

The goal is to prove that the first partial derivative of `f u_outer` with respect to the first coordinate of `P` (the point being rotated) is equal to `inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂θ P) (pc.w)` (which is `⟨pbar.rotM₂θ P, pc.w⟩`).

